[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering server thread issues**\n\nI'm thinking about whether server thread deadlocks could happen because Jetty 10 sends request headers without properly terminating them. That doesn’t seem likely. However, I wonder if the request callback uses ClientHttpRequest::setComplete without a body, while Jetty might be sending an HTTP request with chunked transfers. I think header reading ends at CRLFCRLF anyway, then it won't respond. I'm not entirely sure about the specifics here, but there’s something interesting to unravel!\n\n**Considering dependency compatibility**\n\nI’m thinking the issue arises from test dependency requiring jetty-reactive-httpclient 2.0.6, while Spring 5.3.32 has upgraded to support Jetty 10 and specifically \"requires\" Jetty 10.0.17. This indicates a mismatch between the versions, and I should explore how these dependencies interact. It's crucial to get the right versions in sync to avoid any compatibility issues. I’ll be sure to check the Spring documentation for any updates regarding this transition!\n\n**Updating dependencies**\n\nI’m looking into a setComplete bug in an old Jetty version. I need to update to a newer, supported version. Spring 5.3.32 was released in January 2024 and probably uses Jetty 9.4.53.v20231009. There might be API changes since earlier versions, especially with things like Jetty10HttpFieldsHelper. I should check if updating the dependency version is necessary. I want to avoid hardcoding artifact versions if possible, following the task rules for modifying build.gradle only when needed.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e0983f2998288b6016a26d5d284d481948d5d95d7466c8bde\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJtX3cg4PD3OrR7pKZGmhhljd-PR4XddDelF9h2bby3WPprfsepBtn-OBnJBCSrYx9-bj8O7WcvvvS-ke9q5cB2mkwD0gvUPXkEnEZLNkv1LI88y_ZpDl_r_6Bu9n6-DthsfHq2bNkS3VlOko80nNCrRng68r2zhzGGyV3Tu