's already bounded, but maybe I can widen it with a minimal edit. I don't want to mask any underlying issues; I need to maintain functional coverage.\\n\\nThe test passes under 60 seconds, and 30 seconds could be okay if there's no deadlock. But if no request is sent, the test fails after 30 seconds. I can focus on improving the ServerSocket response without reading the request before writing the response.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Jetty server handling**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how the raw server might wait for the end of headers rather than content. If Jetty doesn't send due to expecting content, then the Content-Length could be set to zero to indicate no body. I could modify the callback to manage this. I might also consider using `writeWith(Flux.empty())`, but I need to check imports, especially for Mono or DataBuffer. The handling of empty responses is a bit tricky, but I'm exploring options!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_MJ8Z7zmpfvgX7TIxQSQDNclm|fc_0e0983f2998288b6016a26d656588881948db09040e331943f", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "rg \"setComplete|JettyClientHttp\" -n tests/src/org.springframework/spring-web/5.3.32/src/test/java"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1038, "output": 1825, "cacheRead": 44032, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46895, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780930086879, "responseId": "resp_0e0983f2998288b6016a26d6278bf48194b87cf5e615e1526d"}}
