[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing server timeout issues**\n\nI’m considering that the startup overhead affects the connection in Continuous Integration (CI) environments. Perhaps the server socket timeout starts after the connection is established, which could explain the delay. The test might fail due to a Jetty delay over 10 seconds from a cold start. Maybe the block timeout is too aggressive with the test taking around 22 seconds total.\n\nI wonder if extending the block timeout to 30 seconds, while keeping individual time under 60 seconds, could help resolve this.\n\n**Resolving timeout issues**\n\nI’m thinking about the timeout and the suggestion to replace unbounded waits with bounded waits. It's already bounded, but maybe I can widen it with a minimal edit. I don't want to mask any underlying issues; I need to maintain functional coverage.\n\nThe test passes under 60 seconds, and 30 seconds could be okay if there's no deadlock. But if no request is sent, the test fails after 30 seconds. I can focus on improving the ServerSocket response without reading the request before writing the response.\n\n**Considering Jetty server handling**\n\nI’m thinking about how the raw server might wait for the end of headers rather than content. If Jetty doesn't send due to expecting content, then the Content-Length could be set to zero to indicate no body. I could modify the callback to manage this. I might also consider using `writeWith(Flux.empty())`, but I need to check imports, especially for Mono or DataBuffer. The handling of empty responses is a bit tricky, but I'm exploring options!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e0983f2998288b6016a26d628be8c8194830dee3ca1b8856c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJtZWnMfMVcJ5WcXkfBoj-nJ49Gg6iEWNpa8xfkrq1bQrF56xLAk6Pryu16WxQ1y3-ZRtE8QmmIHu-E2NAJBVPZlCuzxIInw9sX4NXiULF1q3K5zU3_MLDPEf75WGfbWYJyH3b2k67PEM19gzA3gS