[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Analyzing request handling**\n\nIt seems like the method ClientHttpRequest::setComplete returns Mono<Void> that completes but doesn’t set up the body. I think execute subscribes to that. In Jetty's reactive setup, the request only sends with the downstream request. I'm wondering if a timeout occurs due to an exception in the server thread, especially since the server future isn't being checked. If readHttpRequest throws, then the server Future holds that exception, but the response block keeps waiting until it times out. Could it be that readHttpRequest is the issue?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0e0983f2998288b6016a26d7ffdab88194bb711116b8a2f12f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJtghOd-sf4f4MWxEsh47LGBjCVBeSgQRmdNUAU58rqE8rDetG1ByTf2pQpcaY91ALWz3g4ursToT5SzY-ketl9GUdrzKGgd-GZOiYi0G4LSYJhkXrT73v-2ynIOU2182ldL_UqJUp7r_SilREnn9ZU_3Q-uEmzncfAEhtD-02K3L6HvNI1kFsVS5JezYyC3rLzhFOGez0HeQIPUlX0B6VY3JvgN3zc29Ie7ZlZvUtrmutB2o1Fis083KQ_PS6T1zZefmmNEdo1gOi1vD8UIalUmeDDp1WADEqc4v7Ggc6MWE-n3Hi99j2uwrGyvtK3nvniaFHC0_oC1p-UlkErzAoKl7SLWTPa5bNticmX141YZ-A3wfbA9PpT5q5rcd7OLrrknwK_8s2MVpDq_WeEF2Vd33cyG4KvbqtovnwgeT5x5LmPjupO-ce6IOZGs5Ky-i9KSbUOkhMX3_XlFyN_2q0eTmzgIF0KHa9oih1ZCxYHyXjX6oXEy-NhW93DJLiSXb1E4wrCPExsFG9EV3rcIUIIyVc6i7x7u6o0rHrQAuzhz-giKgHvo4CvRWLPXvxs4EANKhE2VXwB3vu_73XDXW4dvbF-SVoR40BqCWq8t0rMxMMtYAzF7hVnHExRyJIu0lQTfkVid9fLqwyHukpPwMIc7BkIfACb87wpjowpuiqsLEMIw91MvPQ7yhva4ASwRqH3SMgSRTtFKuWKppUxtUhyQSgyCCEJQ4_FcmxgjvU1xbDbwguJ_KqQeSshwD0jZdoHxq3PhcfwQbPrwnONj9dLCkY2k_cXpnDlVkzvbTHnVSuL-7lwKKPjcGsMrIeo-K-g91tFTxFIDl1L6SRlT7ahP-Rr5gXEXY9RRrgYgaOIkGo8cswxS84ZtKkHtoaD38z7FKktc_DYOXrbZoD7ybjhLf7QVyfilmXhyuswWh-tewmCDzHM9xUm4a0x6J_LDWwSccDZQkU-TZRTkqzEkrUV6FJzo735YFu4cLiuo50hL-eTU1pFe5woTTJWeQ_FIgK4KfhuHMl-Wsb5ukwhWfGn_nulVzgI1TYnRpb4FJKKWw61PzBYZQYo0rbaD5__nZ6j6FRe7GZpZ6472vNJmmmyiGNIGogDc6Kng73I0I4TNibSXd5XYAy0smeyhYtOJ0ARk9s