[thinking] I need to fix an issue that's preventing the system from running. It looks like there might be an incompatibility between Jetty reactive httpclient version 2.0.6 and Spring version 5.3.32. The timeout suggests the connector isn’t emitting any signals, possibly because the server isn’t accepting connections. I also want to dig into whether the native test setup is part of the problem—there are references suggesting both JVM and native tests are involved and might be running into timeout errors. I'll explore potential requirements around JettyClientHttpConnector too.
